Symptoms:
- “No space left on device” errors
- Services failing to start
- Can't write files
- Backups failing
- Logs stopped being written

Diagnosis:
df -h
du -sh /opt/docker/* | sort -h
du -sh /var/lib/docker/* | sort -h
docker system df
find /var/log -type f -size +100M

Common Causes:
- Old Docker images/containers/volumes accumulating
- Log files growing unchecked (especially Loki)
- Prometheus/Loki retention too long
- Old backups not cleaned up
- Large files in /tmp not deleted

Solutions:

Clean Docker resources:
docker system prune -a
# Warning: Removes all unused images, containers, networks

Clean old logs:
# Find large log files
find /var/log -type f -size +100M
# Truncate if safe:
sudo truncate -s 0 /var/log/[large-file].log

Delete old backups:
find /opt/backups -type f -mtime +7 -delete

Reduce Loki retention:
ssh [user]@mntr.lab.local
nano /opt/docker/loki-config.yml
# Change retention_period: 30d to 7d or 14d
docker compose restart loki

Reduce Prometheus retention:
nano /opt/docker/docker-compose.yml
# Find prometheus command, add/change:
command:

    '–storage.tsdb.retention.time=7d'

docker compose restart prometheus

Prevention:
- Set up automated cleanup (cron job to delete old backups)
- Configure log rotation
- Set appropriate retention periods from start
- Monitor disk usage in Grafana
